<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.5B.5BPhilip_J._Hilts.5D.5D1996"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Philip_J._Hilts&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Philip J. Hilts (page does not exist)">Philip J. Hilts</a> (1996). <i>Memory's Ghost</i>. New York: Simon &amp; Schuster. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/068482356X" class="internal">ISBN 0-684-82356-X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Memory%27s+Ghost&amp;rft.aulast=%5B%5BPhilip+J.+Hilts%5D%5D&amp;rft.au=%5B%5BPhilip+J.+Hilts%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Simon+%26+Schuster&amp;rft.isbn=0-684-82356-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:HM_(patient)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Provides further discussion of the author's meetings with HM.</li>
</ul>
